message.entry: Select timeseries objects from a dataset based on one of: 'SampleTime', 'TimeVector'.
Select timetables from a dataset based on one of: 'SampleRate', 'TimeStep', or 'RowTimes'.
This method is only valid for scalar Dataset or Signal objects.
The output format must be one of the following: 'timetable', 'cell-by-signal', 'cell-by-sampletime', 'cell-by-timestep'.
The sample time must be specified as a scalar or a vector containing positive numeric values.
The sample rate must be a scalar or a vector containing numeric values, specified in Hz.
The time step must be a scalar or a vector containing duration values.
Combining template with other specifications for selecting data to extract is not supported.
Unable to synchronize the specified data. To output data as a cell array, set 'OutputFormat' to 'cell-by-signal'.
Template must be a timeseries object, timetable, Simulink.SimulationData.Signal, or a character vector or string scalar specifying the name of a dataset element.
Time vector must be specified as a double vector.
Multiple dataset elements have the provided name. Provide a timeseries object, timetable, or Simulink.SimulationData.Signal as the template input to specify which signal is to be used instead.
All timeseries objects extracted from the input must have the same TimeInfo Units, unless 'OutputFormat' is set to 'cell-by-signal'.
